AbstractGrouper<I>
public static class AbstractGrouper.Group<I>
extends IdentityPipe<I>

Models a group. If a sink wants to get elements from a group-operator, it has to subscribe to a special group, otherwise an exception is thrown to indicate that no group has been selected.

Constructor Detail

AbstractGrouper.Group

public AbstractGrouper.Group(Source<? extends I> source,
                             int sourceID)
Creates a new group as an integral part of a group-operator.
The subscription to the specified source (the group-operator) is fulfilled immediately.

Parameters:
source - This pipe gets subscribed to the specified source (group-operator).
ID - This pipe uses the given ID for subscription.
